    <text>
        <body>
           <div type="witness" subtype="poem" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" rhyme="aa">     
                    <lg type="stanza">
                        <l>Oh, are there spirits, can there be</l>
                        <l>Things of such wondrous mystery?</l>
                        <l>Oh, are there spirits, can a mind</l>
                        <l>Float bodiless and unconfined?</l>
                        <l>Or can the air, the earth, the sea</l>
                        <l>Be filled with immortality?</l>
                        <l>Some say that in the cold moonlight</l>
                        <l>There hovereth many a changing sprite.</l>
                        <l>Some say the wind,&#x2014;and who can tell?&#x2014;</l>
                        <l>Bears spirits&#x02BC; voices in its swell.</l>
                        <l>But if upon our mortal sense</l>
                        <l>There rules unearthly influence&#x2014;</l>
                        <l>If there be sprites in earth or air,</l>
                        <l>They surely have their dwelling there.<ref type="gloss_contextual" target="oh_are_there_spirits_can_there_be_poem_glosses_contextual.php#SPRITESINEARTHORAIR"/></l>
                    </lg>
            </div>
